2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The construction of superregular matrices involves certain algorithmic techniques and optimization problems, which are relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The concept of superregular matrices has applications in network coding and communication networks, which are topics covered under the sub-category of social and information networks. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses the size of the finite field needed for the proposed matrices to be superregular, which involves numerical analysis and computations. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The problem of constructing superregular matrices for MDP convolutional codes can be viewed as a computational complexity problem, as it involves finding efficient algorithms for constructing such matrices.
